{{about|the Somali dress|other uses|Dirac (disambiguation)}}

The '''dirac''' is a Somali dress worn by women that is long, usually ankle length, loose-fitting and usually has at least two colors. Its popularity began increasing in the 1970s and 1980s, and during those decades the dirac began replacing the [[guntiino]] in terms of popularity among women.<ref>The Politics of Dress in Somali Culture - Page 82, Heather Marie Akou - 2011</ref> It looks similar to the ''[[grand boubou]]'' worn by women in French-speaking West Africa. It is usually worn along with a [[gorgoro]], an undergarment.<ref>The International Politics of Fashion: Being Fab in a Dangerous World, Andreas Behnke - 2016 p 151</ref>

==See also==
* [[Kufi]] - cap worn in [[West Africa]]
* [[Kanzu]] - tunic worn with the kofia cap in [[East Africa]]

